events.name: Open Source Breakfast Hack
events.description: Join us for breakfast and hack on open source projects at the same time! We will be inviting mentors with experience in Ruby and Rails projects to help you get started or assist you should you get stucked :) If you're a more experienced developer, join us and assist others or pair up with other developers to work on more challenging issues. Here are some ideas for the morning if you don't know what to work on :) # Rails • https://github.com/rails/rails/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22With+reproduction+steps%22 Be sure to get your development environment setup if you're planning to work on Rails https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7zoD6NZy6vY • http://eileencodes.com/posts/getting-your-local-environment-setup-to-contribute-to-rails/  # Ruby • http://documenting-ruby.org/ Find anywhere that is lacking in documentation? Contribute to the Ruby docs and help improve the lives of many developers.  Some other open source Ruby projects that some attendees will be working on.  • Daru - https://github.com/v0dro/daru • Rubocop - https://github.com/bbatsov/rubocop • Discourse - https://github.com/discourse/discourse
events.location: The Hub, Cuppage, 21A Cuppage Terrace S229452, Singapore

events.name: Let's share ideas on Bio-Making & discuss how to develop a BioScience Community
events.description: Join us at MakerFaire SG for our second public event (you may have met us at Tech Saturday last month). We have an exhibit stall in the Tech section of MF this weekend Sat and Sun[masked]hrs. In addition to showcasing our equipment and projects, we will conduct 15-min demo's on the hour between 11am and 5pm: • Learn how to Mod and Improv a Biolab for under $100 • See what Microbes are Used in our Food • Get tips on Culturing Bacteria and Fungi at Home We will also be making available Microbial Culture Kits for the first time. We're keen to share ideas on how as a BioScience Community we can explore and catalog the Diversity of Microbiomes in our Food and Environment. More importantly, as we have received tremendous interest, we are considering launching a series of monthly meet-ups and projects. What are your interests and needs? What have you been doing or hope to try? How can a community of scientists and amateurs help you? Would hands-on workshops be of interest? Prof Eric and Dr Siva from NTU are keen to chat with you.  More info at: www.OpenBio.asia
events.location: SUTD Multi-Purpose Hall, 8 Somapah Road, Singapore

events.name: Shapeways @ Singapore Maker Faire 2016
events.description: Not really a meetup but we'll be having some booths (with our friends) and have a showcase of some of the awesome 3d printed stuff from Shapeways over at Singapore Makers Faire 2016! It's a family friendly festival of invention, creativity and resourcefulness happening over at STUD.  So do come by and join in the fun! =) Official Website - https://makerfairesingapore.com/ See you there! =)
events.location: Singapore University of Technology and Design, 8 Somapah Road
